
rsyn -av /etc/  ~/etc/backup/	--> will copy folder recursively..when source file is changed,running rsync again only copies whats been added or modified..
rsyn -av --delete /etc/  ~/etc/backup/	--> this will delete files on destination when deleted from source


Note: when source directory has trailing slash,only the contents of the source directory will be copied otherwise the whole directory will be copied.


rsync -av --exclude-from='fileThatCOntainsFilesToExclude' my_project/ backup/		--> excluding files in rsync
or

rsync -av --exclude='*.png' my_project/ backup/



